{{Infobox prepared food | name = Bolo de mel | image = "Bolo de mel" cakes, Madeira.jpg | image_size = 300px | caption = | alternate_name = Bolo de cana de mel | country = [[Portugal]] | region = [[Madeira]] | creator = Renato José dos Santos | type = [[Cake]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[Flour]], [[sugar]], [[butter]] or [[margarine]], [[lard]], [[molasses]] or [[honey]], [[walnut]]s, [[almond]]s, [[spices]] | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''''Bolo de mel''''' ({{IPA-pt|ˈbolu ðɨ ˈmɛɫ}}, "honey cake") is a traditional cake from the [[Madeira|Madeira Islands]].
==History== This cake is considered to be Madeira's oldest dessert. Started up by Renato José dos Santos, who baked and decorated [[wedding cakes]] at {{lang|pt|Fábrica da Estrela}} before its fire of 1964. He proceeded to open his own factory in Rochinha Madeira, baking {{lang|pt|bolo de mel}}, sugared almonds, {{lang|pt|torradas}} (toasts, some recipes call for sweet buns) and {{lang|pt|[[broa]]s}} (breads with cornmeal in the recipe, also made with molasses).{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
==Ingredients== The {{lang|pt|bolo de mel}} cake became a popular confection when the island was an important sugar producer, since the cake itself is traditionally made with [[molasses]] instead of the now-popular [[honey]], which meant it could be stored for up to 5 years.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}} When made with molasses, the cake is very dark in color and has a spongy sticky texture resembling a soft [[cookie]]. The cake often has [[walnuts]] and [[almond]]s mixed within it. When it is served in Madeira, it is customary not to cut the cake, but rather to tear pieces off using the hands.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
{{lang|pt|Bolo de mel}} is traditionally made during [[Christmas]] often in a large enough batch that it can be enjoyed throughout the year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bolo-de-mel.com/bolo-de-mel.html |title=Bolo de Mel |accessdate=2013-09-20 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053902/http://www.bolo-de-mel.com/bolo-de-mel.html |archivedate=2013-09-21 }}</ref>
