{{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Doctor Dolittle's Zoo | title_orig = | translator = | image = File:DoctorDolittlesZoo.jpg | caption = First edition | author = [[Hugh Lofting]] | illustrator = Hugh Lofting | cover_artist = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | series = [[Doctor Dolittle]] | subject = | genre = [[Children's literature|Children's novel]] | publisher = [[Frederick A. Stokes]] | release_date = 1926 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]] & [[Paperback]]) | pages = | preceded_by = [[Doctor Dolittle's Circus]] | followed_by = [[Doctor Dolittle's Caravan]] }} {{Portal |Children's literature}}
'''''Doctor Dolittle's Zoo''''' was written and illustrated by [[Hugh Lofting]] in 1926. In the book, [[Doctor Dolittle]] returns from his voyages and sets his house in order. This includes expanding his zoo to include a home for crossbred dogs and a club for rodents. The doctor also takes time to solve a mystery with the aid of Kling, the Dog Detective.
