{{Infobox station |name = Rustaveli |type = {{TBILISIMETRO type}} |image = Metro Rustaveli.jpg |image_size = |image_caption = |address = |coordinates = {{coord|41|42|13|N|44|47|24|E|display=title,inline}} |line = {{TBILISIMETRO-line1}} |other = |structure = |platform = 1 |depth = {{convert|60|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} |levels = 1 |tracks = 2 |opened = {{date|1966-01-11|dmy}} |closed = |rebuilt = |electrified = Yes |zone = |former = |passengers = |pass_year = |pass_percent = |pass_system = |mpassengers = |services = {{s-rail|title=Tbilisi Metro}} {{s-line|system=TBILISIMETRO|line=Akhmeteli-Varketili|previous=Marjanishvili|next=Tavisuplebis Moedani}} |map_locator = }} {{stack|{{Akhmeteli-Varketili Line}}}} The '''Rustaveli''' ({{lang-ka|რუსთაველი}}) is a station of the [[Tbilisi metro]] on the [[Akhmeteli-Varketili Line]]. It is located at Rustaveli square at the northern end of [[Rustaveli avenue]]. The station was opened on 11 January 1966 as part of the first metro line with six stations from [[Didube (Tbilisi Metro)|Didube]] to Rustaveli. Located between [[Tavisuplebis Moedani (Tbilisi Metro)|Tavisuplebis Moedani station]] and [[Marjanishvili (Tbilisi Metro)|Marjanishvili station]], Rustaveli is with 60 meters (and an escalator length of 120 meters) the deepest station of the Tbilisi metro system.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metro.ge/index.php?sec_id=128&lang_id=ENG|title=Metro in figures|publisher=Tbilisi Metro|accessdate=3 February 2010}}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
